<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-82-0999 </DOCNO><TEXT>The diagnostic value of nuclear medical examinations significantly dependson the efficiency of the examination technique as a whole, and on theefficiency of the various scanning and measuring instruments. Systematicequipment quality control is a must in order to guarantee the requiredquality, and such quality controls cover acceptance tests, consistencytesting, and standard performance measurements. The testing methods appliedfor scintillation spectrometers and gamma cameras are explained in detail.</TEXT></DOC>